dashboardItems.text:
*Definitions*

*Report completeness (%)* 

Numerator = Actual health facilities reporting/

Denominator = Expected health facilities to report

*Report timeliness (%)* 

Numerator = Actual health facilities reporting on time

Denominator = Actual health facilities reporting

*Completeness by variables (%)* 

Numerator = Count of values reported for key data value that is representative of the data element

Denominator = Expected reports from all health facilities assign the dataSet that reports the variable

*Interpretations*


Consistency between variables here is being measured by computing the difference between two related data elements that would typically be validated with validation rules.


In this case, inconsistencies between data elements are when the difference between these variables is negative or the value of the left-side variable is more than the right-side and this would be flagged red.
